    "body": "ubuntu default is 1024 file descriptors. TCP timeout wait default is 60 seconds opening a new file descriptor on each tcp connect and will linger for 60 seconds. I would expect this issue with a high amount of rcp connects from ethminers, etc. Also, i've noticed that improper kills, not just the one exiting, leaves open descriptors that pile on top each other on each restart until the limit is reached. \n",
